collation.p:
Originally 19 quires, now 20, after quire 8 was divided and rebound as two. The final quire is a later restoration. A 
                            replacement of 12 leaves (13th century scribal hand), sometime after the primary leaves broke off along inner rulings, 
                            has disrupted the original structure of 8 leaves per quire. Restored leaves were inserted as follows: Leaf 5, quire 1 (fol. 5); 
                            leaf 2, quire 2 (fol. 10); leaf 1, quire 5 (fol. 33); leaves 4-6, quire 6 (fols. 44-46); leaf 5 and leaf 8, quire 7 (fol. 53, fol. 56); 
                            leaves 6-8, quire 8 (fols. 62-64); leaf 6, quire 9 (fol. 70).

Originally 19 quires, now 20, after quire 8 was divided and rebound as two. The final quire is a later restoration. A 
        replacement of 12 leaves (13th century scribal hand), sometime after the primary leaves broke off along inner rulings, 
        has disrupted the original structure of 8 leaves per quire. Restored leaves were inserted as follows: Leaf 5, quire 1 (fol. 5); 
        leaf 2, quire 2 (fol. 10); leaf 1, quire 5 (fol. 33); leaves 4-6, quire 6 (fols. 44-46); leaf 5 and leaf 8, quire 7 (fol. 53, fol. 56); 
        leaves 6-8, quire 8 (fols. 62-64); leaf 6, quire 9 (fol. 70).
